DEF 1="dmkr_admin"

-- Documaker Assembly Line Database File Location

-- AssemblyLine Id:

-- ACCEPT 2 default '1' prompt 'Enter the System Id:'

----- DROP USER &3. CASCADE;
----- DROP TABLESPACE &3. -- INCLUDING CONTENTS;
----- remove the &3..dbf after dropping TABLESPACE;


WHENEVER SQLERROR EXIT SQL.SQLCODE; 

ALTER SYSTEM SET DB_CREATE_FILE_DEST = '&5.';

CREATE SMALLFILE TABLESPACE &3. DATAFILE '&5.&3..dbf' SIZE 200M AUTOEXTEND ON NEXT 1M MAXSIZE 2G LOGGING EXTENT MANAGEMENT LOCAL SEGMENT SPACE MANAGEMENT AUTO;

CREATE USER &3.
    IDENTIFIED BY &4.
    DEFAULT TABLESPACE &3.
    TEMPORARY TABLESPACE TEMP
    PROFILE DEFAULT 
    ACCOUNT UNLOCK 
;

GRANT CONNECT, CREATE ANY INDEX, RESOURCE, CREATE PROCEDURE, CREATE SEQUENCE, CREATE SESSION, CREATE SYNONYM, CREATE TABLE, CREATE TRIGGER, CREATE VIEW, UNLIMITED TABLESPACE TO &3.
;
GRANT CONNECT, CREATE ANY INDEX, RESOURCE, CREATE PROCEDURE, CREATE SEQUENCE, CREATE SESSION, CREATE SYNONYM, CREATE TABLE, CREATE TRIGGER, CREATE VIEW, UNLIMITED TABLESPACE TO &1.
;


GRANT SELECT ON &1..ALCONFIGCONTEXT TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..ALS TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..APPCONFIGCONTEXT TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..APPS TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..SYSCONFIGCONTEXT TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..SYSS TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..CONFIGCONTEXTLOG TO &3.;

GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_ABILITIES TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_ABILITIES_TRANSLATIONS TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_ABILITYSETS TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_ABILITYSET_ABILITY TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_ABILITYTYPES TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_APPRLEVELSENTITIES TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_APPROVERLEVELS TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_TRANSLAT TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_ENTITIES TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_ENTITYTYPE_TRANSLATIONS TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_ENTITY_ABILITYSET TO &3.;
GRANT SELECT ON &1..DMKR_ENTITY_TO_ENTITY TO &3.;

COMMENT ON TABLE BCHINGS IS 'Batchings table, defines one or more BCHS.BCHNAMEs for a RCPS.BATCHNAME as well as immediate vs. schedule print and the scheduling info.  '
;

;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BATCHNAME IS 'Batch Name associated to the RCPS.BATCHNAME column' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BATCHTYPE IS 'Batch Type associated to the RCPS.BATCHTYPE column' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGNAME IS 'Batching Names used to name the BCHS rows for BCHNAME to give the batch 
record a identifiable name' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGACTIVE IS 'Batching is Active or inactive
0=Inactive
1=Active (default)' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGTYPE IS '0=Immediate Batch (default)
1=Scheduled Batch' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGSELECTRULE IS 'Selection for batch rule. typically a WHERE clause on the RCPS table.
Has to have the table name in it to qualify it so it can use TRNS and RCPS.
Used for additional SELECT criteria for associating a RCPS 
with a Batch BCH_ID.  If not NULL gets run by the Batcher when 
adding records to the batch.  
' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGPRTTYPE IS 'Output Type for the Batch (PDF, PS, AFP, XER, TXT, HTML, EPT (HTML email), VPP, ...)' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGPRTTYPERULE IS 'Selection of the PRTTYPE for a BCHS batch. 
Typically a column in RCPS or TRNS where the value defines the print type.  
Has to have the table name in it to qualify it so it can use JOBS,TRNS or RCPS.
NULL or empty implies BCHINGPRTTYPE decides. 
Default is Batcher configuration if BCHINGPRTTYPE and this column are NULL or empty.
when the BCHS.BCHPRTTYPE is set.  ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGSORTRULE IS 'Rule to be run by the Batcher to sequence the BCHS_RCPS in a sorting order 
that the admin chooses for the batch.  
Typically a RCPS column name like RCPS.ADR_POSTALCODE is set to sort a 
scheduled batch by the postal code.  
Should be a table qualified name so that other tables 
are candidates in a multitable select call, e.g. FROM BCHS,JOBS,TRNS,RCPS.
This becomes a ORDER BY clause in the select statement if provided to override 
any sorting the system does normally.  A comma delmiited list of columns and 
ASC and DEC key words can be used to as in a ORDER BY clause.' 
;

;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGDOM IS 'Day of Month, 0 or null meaning not used.
1-28,29,30 or 31
Use with MOY to specify a specific month and day,

BCHINGMOY=4 
BCHINGDOM=15
April 15th every year'

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGSTARTYEAR IS 'Starting Year of Batch.
0 or null means no delay on year to start.
Otherwise controls when the batcher will start using the batch. 
Only applies if the BCHINGACTIVE is set to True. 
Usually combined with BCHINGSTARTMONTH and BCHINGSTARTDAY to 
specify when the batch starts getting processed in the future so it can be setup 
sooner and not activated by the system until it is time. ' 
;

Usually combined with BCHINGSTARTYEAR and BCHINGSTARTMONTH to

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGSTARTMINUTES IS 'Starting minutes of the Batch.

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGENDDATE IS 'Ending Date of Batch, null means no end.  
System will typically mark batch as inactive via the BCHINGACTIVE flag 
once the Ending date has been reached so that the batch no longer has to be 
evaluated after it has passed its ending date.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGBREAKTYPE IS 'Break batch, output type indicator, copied to BCHS for processing.
0,null=None
1=by sheet count
2=by rcp count
3=by page count
4=by transaction count
5=by custom script based' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGBREAKVALUE IS 'Break batch to new output pubs row value indicator.
When break type is:
0 or null then not applicable
1 then use this sheet count static value or GVM variable or DAL value to compare against the running sheet count to break the batch
2 then use this rcp count static value or GVM variable or DAL value to compare against the running rcp count to break the batch
3 then use this page count static value or GVM variable or DAL value to compare against the running page count to break the batch
4 thenuse this transaction count static value or GVM variable or DAL value to compare against the running transaction count to break the batch transaction count value to break the batch
5 then use a script and when the return value is TRUE then break the batch' 
;

0=Not a Archive Batch (default)
1=Archive Batch 
BCHS row will inherit the BCHARCHIVE value that is the same.
'

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGPUBLISH IS 'Boolean to indicate that a batch is actually for publication 
with this value set to True, 1, the batch created will go to the
Output Publisher for distribution to printers or other targets.
Typically set to False, 0, when the output, spool data, in the 
PUB rows is for archive (with or without notification) 
but not for actual publication printing or any Publisher actions.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGMIMETYPE IS 'MIME type indicator for the batch that gets propagated to the 
PUBS rows to define the MIME type of the print spool or other 
output stored in the row.  Ususally used for printing by the 
Output Publisher for print device routing.  ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGPRTLOGNAME IS 'Logical Printer Name' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGPUBEMAIL IS 'If set to true (1) will send the published output as an attachment to a email.
Email rule can override this value by being not null and returning 1 or 0 when evaluated allowing input data to override the 
batch level setting.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGPUBEMAILRULE IS 'If defined then must return a numerical value.  Numerical value but 0 
evaluates as true and will send the published output as an attachment to an email.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGPUBLANGRULE IS 'Rule to be run by the Publisher to determine the language of the 
email message text and HTML when one is selected.  Typically a RCPS column name like 
RCPS.ADR_LANGUAGE.  Should be a table qualified name so that other tables 
are candidates in a multitable select call, e.g. FROM TRNS,RCPS ...' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGPUBMSGTYPRULE IS 'Message type selection rule 
for the text and HTML part of the mime email to send with the attached published output.
The value returned from this column is used to select the template by 
the PUBNTFS.PUBNTFMSGTYP value.  Either a static value or a column from JOBS, TRNS, RCPS can be used. ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGENABLENTF IS 'This boolean indicates that the Batch can have Notification ability (SMS or EMAIL).
0=Not a candidate for Notification (default)
1=Allows Notification
This value will be populated into the BCHS.BCHNOTIFY column when it is created.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGNTFRULE IS 'Notification rule run when the BCHINGENABLENTF=1 is set by the Publisher for Notifications
the BCH_ID passed to determine if a Recipient has requested a Notification.  
Should return rows in the RCPS tables that are associated with the batch that have requested a Notification 
by returning a notification type if Notification type IN SMS, MMS, OR EMAIL.
Typically a column or a where clause on the RCPS table. 
The publisher for notification will check to see if the RCPS.RCPOUTBLOB is NULL. 
If it is it will generate the message from the message template for the 
language specified by the RCPS.ADR_LANGUAGE and store it in the RCPS.RCPOUTBLOB column 
for the row for the RCP_ID.  If the RCPS.RCPPUTBLOB is not NULL then a notification
for the TRN_ID,RCP_ID has already been sent so no need to send it again.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGLANGRULE IS 'Rule to be run by the Publisher for Notification to determine the language of the 
Notification when one is selected.  Typically a RCPS column name like 
RCPS.ADR_LANGUAGE.  Should be a table qualified name so that other tables 
are candidates in a multitable select call, e.g. FROM TRNS,RCPS ...' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHINGS.BCHINGNTFMSGTYPRULE IS 'Message type selection rule.
The value returned from this column is used to select the template by 
the PUBNTFS.PUBNTFMSGTYP value.  
Either a static value or a column from JOBS, TRNS, RCPS can be used. ' 
;

COMMENT ON TABLE BCHS IS 'Batching Table, a batch is a collection of Recipient records (RCPS) for a specific distribution purpose.
Could be scheduled where it collects recipents for later processing on a schedule or it could be immediate.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCH_ID IS 'Batch Unique Identifier' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHNAME IS 'Name for Batch record' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHUNIQUE_ID IS 'Unique GUID for application lookup' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHSTARTINGTIME IS 'Scheduled Batch Starting Time' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHSTATUS IS 'Status of processing the BCHS row (Batch).' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHSEQ IS 'Order of BCHS for sequencing when there are dependancies between batches.
Used for sequencing schedule to Output Manager.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHTYPE IS '0=Immediate Batch
1=Scheduled Batch ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHBATCHNAME IS 'Batch Name associated to the RCPS.BATCHNAME column' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHBATCHTYPE IS 'Batch Type associated to the RCPS.BATCHTYPE column' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHBY IS 'Details about how the batch of recipient records were ordered, 
e.g. by recipient, by weight, by page count, by ...' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHSELECTRULE IS 'Selection for batch rule. typically a WHERE clause on the RCPS table.

;

;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHSTARTTIME IS 'When the recipient processing started for the batch.  Statistical.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHENDTIME IS 'When the recipient processing ended for the batch, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHTRNCOUNT IS 'Total number of transactions in the batch.  Statistical.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHRCPCOUNT IS 'Total number of recipent in the batch.  Statistical.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPAGECOUNT IS 'Total number of pages in the recipient rows in the batch, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHSHEETCOUNT IS 'Total number of sheets in the recipient rows in the batch, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHBREAKTYPE IS 'Break batch, output type indicator.
0,null=None
1=by sheet count
2=by rcp count
3=by page count
4=by transaction count
5=by custom script based' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHBREAKVALUE IS 'Break batch to new output pubs row value indicator.
When break type is:
0 or null then not applicable
1 then use this sheet count static value or GVM variable or DAL value to compare against the running sheet count to break the batch
2 then use this rcp count static value or GVM variable or DAL value to compare against the running rcp count to break the batch
3 then use this page count static value or GVM variable or DAL value to compare against the running page count to break the batch
4 thenuse this transaction count static value or GVM variable or DAL value to compare against the running transaction count to break the batch transaction count value to break the batch
5 then use a script and when the return value is TRUE then break the batch' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHARCHIVE IS 'Batch is marked for Archival' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHARCDEST IS 'Batch Level control for Archival Destiniation' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBTOTALARC IS 'Total Publish table rows marked for archive (based on BCHTYPES table).' ;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBERRARC IS 'Current counter of error Archived Publish table rows that were marked for archive. ' ;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBPROCARC IS 'Current counter of successfully Archived Publish table rows that were marked for archive. ' ;


COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHSIGNING IS 'Batch is marked for Signing' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHSGNDEST IS 'Batch Level control for Signing Destiniation' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHSGNTMPL IS 'Batch Signing Template Reference. ' ;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBTOTALSGN IS 'Total Publish table rows marked for archive (based on BCHTYPES table).' ;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBERRSGN IS 'Current counter of error Archived Publish table rows that were marked for archive. ' ;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBPROCSGN IS 'Current counter of successfully Archived Publish table rows that were marked for archive. ' ;


COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBLISH IS 'Boolean to indicate that a batch is actually for publication 
with this value set to True, 1, the batch created will go to the
Output Publisher for distribution to printers or other targets.
Typically set to False, 0, when the output, spool data, in the 
PUB rows is for archive (with or without notification) 
but not for actual publication printing or any Publisher actions.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHMIMETYPE IS 'MIME type indicator for the batch that gets propagated to the 
PUBS rows to define the MIME type of the print spool or other 
output stored in the row.  Ususally used for printing by the 
Output Publisher for print device routing.  ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPRTLOGNAME IS 'Batch Logical Printer name.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBEMAIL IS 'Batch distribute publication through email with attachment print output.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBEMAILRULE IS 'Batch distribute publication through email rule.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBLANGRULE IS 'Batch distribute publication through email using this laguage for email HTML template.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBMSGTYPRULE IS 'Batch distribute publication email message type selection rule
The value returned from this column is used to select the template by 
the PUBNTFS.PUBNTFMSGTYP value.  
Either a static value or a column from JOBS, TRNS, RCPS can be used. ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBTOTALDST IS 'Total Publish table rows generated from this batch.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBERRDST IS 'Counter of currently processed publication table rows for print distribution that were in error ';

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBPROCDST IS 'Counter of currently processed publication table rows for print distribution that were successfully processed' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHENABLENTF IS 'Batch is marked as a Notification enabled batch' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHNTFRULE IS 'Notification rule run when the BCHINGENABLENTF=1 is set by the Publishing 
Notifier.  
Should return rows in the RCPS tables that are associated with the 
batch that have requested a Notification by returning a notification type if 
Notification type in SMS, MMS, OR EMAIL.
Typically a column or a where clause on the RCPS table. 
The publishing notifier will check to see if the RCPS.RCPOUTTYPE IS NULL 
OR (RCPS.RCPOUTTYPE=0 AND RCPS.RCPOUTBLOB IS NULL) 
OR (RCPS.RCPOUTTYPE=1 AND RCPS.RCPOUTREF IS NULL). 
If TRUE  it will generate the message from the message template for the 
language specified by the RCPS.ADR_LANGUAGE and store it in the 
RCPS.RCPOUTBLOB column for the row for the RCP_ID.  
If FALSE then a notification for the TRN_ID,RCP_ID has already been 
sent so no need to send it again.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHLANGRULE IS 'Rule to be run by the Publisher for Notification to determine the language of the 
Notification when one is selected.  Typically a RCPS column name like 
RCPS.ADR_LANGUAGE.  Should be a table qualified name so that other tables 
are candidates in a multitable select call, e.g. FROM TRNS,RCPS ...' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHNTFMSGTYPRULE IS 'Message type selection rule.
The value returned from this column is used to select the template by 
the PUBNTFS.PUBNTFMSGTYP value.  
Either a static value or a column from JOBS, TRNS, RCPS can be used. ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBTOTALNTF IS 'Total number of Publication table rows create marked for Notify based on BCHTYPES setting with notify candidate set and notification specified in the RCP record' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBERRNTF IS 'Current number of Publication table rows with error on Notifications'

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS.BCHPUBPROCNTF IS 'Current number of Publication table rows with sucessful Notifications'

    )

    ADD CONSTRAINT BCHS_PK PRIMARY KEY ( BCH_ID ) ;

    ADD CONSTRAINT BCHS_UNIQUE_ID UNIQUE ( BCHUNIQUE_ID ) 
;


CREATE TABLE BCHSHIST 
    ( 
     BCH_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     BCHNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHUNIQUE_ID NVARCHAR2 (47) , 
     BCHSTARTINGTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHSTATUS NUMBER (10) , 
     BCHSEQ NUMBER (10) , 
     BCHTYPE NUMBER (10) , 
     BCHBATCHNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHBATCHTYPE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHBY NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHSELECTRULE NVARCHAR2 (2000) , 
     BCHPRTTYPE NVARCHAR2 (30) , 
     BCHPRTTYPERULE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHSORTRULE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHMODIFYTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHERRTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHTRNCOUNT NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHRCPCOUNT NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPAGECOUNT NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHSHEETCOUNT NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHWEIGHT NUMBER (19,4) , 
     BCHBREAKTYPE NUMBER (10) , 
     BCHBREAKVALUE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHARCHIVE NUMBER (5) , 
     BCHARCDEST NVARCHAR2 (512) , 
     BCHPUBTOTALARC NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPUBERRARC NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPUBPROCARC NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHSIGNING NUMBER (5) , 
     BCHSGNDEST NVARCHAR2 (512) , 
     BCHSGNTMPL NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHPUBTOTALSGN NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPUBERRSGN NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPUBPROCSGN NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPUBLISH NUMBER (5) , 
     BCHMIMETYPE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHPRTLOGNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHPUBEMAIL NUMBER (5) , 
     BCHPUBEMAILRULE NVARCHAR2 (2000) , 
     BCHPUBLANGRULE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHPUBMSGTYPRULE NVARCHAR2 (2000) , 
     BCHPUBTOTALDST NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPUBERRDST NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPUBPROCDST NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHENABLENTF NUMBER (5) , 
     BCHNTFRULE NVARCHAR2 (2000) ,

     BCHNTFMSGTYPRULE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHPUBTOTALNTF NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPUBERRNTF NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHPUBPROCNTF NUMBER (38) , 
     BCHERR_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     CALLBACK NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BATCHBANNERBEGINSCRIPT NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BATCHBANNERENDSCRIPT NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BATCHBANNERBEGINFORM NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BATCHBANNERENDFORM NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     TRANSBANNERBEGINSCRIPT NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     TRANSBANNERENDSCRIPT NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     TRANSBANNERBEGINFORM NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     TRANSBANNERENDFORM NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPDATE001 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHAPPDATE002 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHAPPDATE003 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHAPPDATE004 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHAPPDATE005 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHAPPDEC001 NUMBER (19,4) , 
     BCHAPPDEC002 NUMBER (19,4) , 
     BCHAPPDEC003 NUMBER (19,4) , 
     BCHAPPDEC004 NUMBER (19,4) , 
     BCHAPPDEC005 NUMBER (19,4) , 
     BCHAPPINT001 NUMBER (20) , 
     BCHAPPINT002 NUMBER (20) , 
     BCHAPPINT003 NUMBER (20) , 
     BCHAPPINT004 NUMBER (20) , 
     BCHAPPINT005 NUMBER (20) , 
     BCHAPPSTR001 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPSTR002 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPSTR003 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPSTR004 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPSTR005 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPSTR006 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPSTR007 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPSTR008 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPSTR009 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHAPPSTR010 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHCUSDATE001 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHCUSDATE002 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHCUSDATE003 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHCUSDATE004 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHCUSDATE005 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHCUSDEC001 NUMBER (19,4) ,

CREATE TABLE BCHS_RCPS 
    ( 
     BCH_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     RCP_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     TRN_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     JOB_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     PUB_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     RCPSEQ NUMBER (10) , 
     BCHRCPTYPE NUMBER (10) ,
     BCHRCPACTIVE NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 1 ,
     BCHRCPBNDLLOC NUMBER (10) , 
     BCHRCPCNTL NVARCHAR2 (10) , 
     BCHRCPCREATETIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHRCPERRTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHRCPPROCTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHRCPSTATUS NUMBER(10) DEFAULT 415, 
     BCHRCPCUSDATE001 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHRCPCUSINT001 NUMBER (20) , 
     BCHRCPCUSDEC001 NUMBER (19,4) , 
     BCHRCPCUSSTR001 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHRCPCUSSTR002 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHRCPGRPSEQ NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 0, 
     BCHRCPGRPTOT NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 0, 
     BCHRCPHISTORY NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 1 , 
     BCHRCPHISTORICAL NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0
    ) 
;


COMMENT ON TABLE BCHS_RCPS IS 'Many-to-many relationship table, a.k.a. association table , that allows any RCPS rows (recipient) to be associate with many 
different BCH rows (batches).  A recipient record can be in many different batch records. '
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPACTIVE IS 'Boolean flag to inactivate recipient from a batch for handling errors or reprint situations.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPBNDLLOC IS 'Bundle relative location to track where in the bundle the recipient 
is located (100=beginning, 500=middle, 900=end). ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPCREATETIME IS 'Time when the Recipent was added to the batch.  ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPERRTIME IS 'Time when error processing Recipient occured in the batch.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPSTATUS IS 'Last Status state of the batch the Recipient is in.' 
;


COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPPROCTIME IS 'Time when the Recipent was completely processed in the 
batch.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPCUSDATE001 IS 'A custom date and time column.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPCUSINT001 IS 'A custom signed integer column.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPCUSDEC001 IS 'A custom decimal column.. 
Used for monitory values or other decimal values with less than 
4 decimals of precision.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPCUSSTR001 IS 'A custom string column' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPCUSSTR002 IS 'A custom string column' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPGRPSEQ IS 'Grouping Sequence Number counter' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPGRPTOT IS 'Grouping Sequence Total value' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPHISTORY IS '1 True by default.  
Indicates if the bchs_rcps row data is to be copied to history table 
upon deletion.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN BCHS_RCPS.BCHRCPHISTORICAL IS 'Indicator that BCHS_RCPS row is in the HISTORY table.
Defaults to FALSE (0) and when inserted into the BCHS_RCPSHIST defaults to 
TRUE (1).  Must be reset to FALSE (0) if data is taken from thei History 
and reprocessed in the active tables. ' 
;
CREATE INDEX BCHS_RCPS_RCPSEQ ON BCHS_RCPS 
    ( 
     BCH_ID ASC , 
     RCPSEQ ASC 
    ) 
;

CREATE INDEX BCHS_RCPS_IDX2 ON BCHS_RCPS 
    ( 
     BCH_ID ASC , 
     RCP_ID ASC 
    ) 
;

CREATE INDEX BCHS_RCPS_TRN_ID ON BCHS_RCPS 
    ( 
     TRN_ID ASC 
    ) 
;


ALTER TABLE BCHS_RCPS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT BCHS_RCPS__IDX PRIMARY KEY ( BCH_ID, RCP_ID, TRN_ID ) ;


CREATE TABLE BCHS_RCPSHIST 
    ( 
     BCH_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     RCP_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     TRN_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     JOB_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     PUB_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     RCPSEQ NUMBER (10) ,
     BCHRCPTYPE NUMBER (10) ,
     BCHRCPACTIVE NUMBER (5),
     BCHRCPBNDLLOC NUMBER (10) , 
     BCHRCPCNTL NVARCHAR2 (10) , 
     BCHRCPCREATETIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHRCPERRTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHRCPPROCTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHRCPSTATUS NUMBER(10), 
     BCHRCPCUSDATE001 TIMESTAMP , 
     BCHRCPCUSINT001 NUMBER (20) , 
     BCHRCPCUSDEC001 NUMBER (19,4) , 
     BCHRCPCUSSTR001 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHRCPCUSSTR002 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BCHRCPGRPSEQ NUMBER (10) , 
     BCHRCPGRPTOT NUMBER (10) , 
     BCHRCPHISTORY NUMBER (5) , 
     BCHRCPHISTORICAL NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 1 
    ) 
;



COMMENT ON TABLE BCHS_RCPSHIST IS 'Many-to-many relationship table, a.k.a. association table , that allows any RCPS rows (recipient) to be associate with many 
different BCH rows (batches).  A recipient record can be in many different batch records. '
;

ALTER TABLE BCHS_RCPSHIST 
    ADD CONSTRAINT BCHS_RCPSHIST_IDX PRIMARY KEY ( BCH_ID, RCP_ID, TRN_ID ) ;


CREATE TABLE ERRS 
    ( 
     ERR_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     JOB_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     TRN_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     BCH_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     RCP_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     PUB_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     ERROR_CODE NVARCHAR2 (15) , 
     ERRCODE1 NVARCHAR2 (10) , 
     ERRCODE2 NVARCHAR2 (10) , 
     ERRAREA NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ERRDATA NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ERRMESSAGE NVARCHAR2 (2000) , 
     ERRTIME TIMESTAMP  NOT NULL , 
     ERRHOSTNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ERRPROGRAM NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ERRVERSION NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ERRMODULE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ERRPROCESS_ID NVARCHAR2 (10) , 
     ERRTHREAD_ID NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ERRCATEGORY NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ERRTAG_ID NVARCHAR2 (256) 
    ) 
;



COMMENT ON TABLE ERRS IS 'Table to log errors'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN ERRS.ERR_ID IS 'Unique auto generated error row identifier' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN ERRS.JOB_ID IS 'JOB_ID foreign key when error is related to the JOGS row' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN ERRS.TRN_ID IS 'TRN_ID foreign key when error is related to the TRNS row' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN ERRS.BCH_ID IS 'BCH_ID foreign key when error is related to the BCHS row' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN ERRS.RCP_ID IS 'RCP_ID foreign key when error is related to the RCPS row' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN ERRS.ERRDATA IS 'Delimited Error Data used for generating translatable error 
messages, typically variable that go into a translated message 
that does not get translated. ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN ERRS.ERRPROCESS_ID IS 'Process Id of the error logger' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN ERRS.ERRTAG_ID IS 'Used to tag and follow error entries for a application or a workflow' 
;

ALTER TABLE ERRS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT ERRS_PK PRIMARY KEY ( ERR_ID ) ;


CREATE TABLE JOBS 
    ( 
     JOB_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     JOBNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     JOBPRIORITY NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 10  NOT NULL , 
     JOBSTATUS NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 0  NOT NULL , 
     JOBUNIQUE_ID NVARCHAR2 (47) , 
     JOBPRTLOGNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     JOBPAYLOADTYPE NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 0  NOT NULL , 
     JOBPAYLOADREF NVARCHAR2 (512) , 
     JOBPAYLOADBLOB BLOB , 
     JOBPAYLOADXML XMLTYPE , 
     JOBATTACHMENTS BLOB , 
     JOBSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBERR_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBTRNTOTAL NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     JOBTRNWIP NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     JOBTRNERR NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     JOBTRNSCH NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0,
     JOBTRNPROC NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 ,
     JOBTRNSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBTRNENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBRCPTOTAL NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     JOBRCPERR NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     JOBRCPSCH NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 ,
     JOBRCPPROC NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 ,
     JOBRCPSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBRCPENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBBCHTOTAL NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     JOBBCHERR NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     JOBBCHSCH NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0,
     JOBBCHPROC NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 ,
     JOBBCHSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBBCHENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBRETENTION TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBRETHOLD NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0 , 
     JOBHISTORY NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 1 , 
     JOBHISTORICAL NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0 ,
     JOBREPLYTOURI NVARCHAR2 (512) ,
     JOBREPLYSENT NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0 ,
     JOBREPLYSENTTIME TIMESTAMP 
    ) 
    LOB ("JOBPAYLOADBLOB") STORE AS SECUREFILE
    (
      NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
      STORAGE(
          MINEXTENTS 1 
          MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
          PCTINCREASE 0 
          FREELISTS 1 
          FREELIST GROUPS 1 
          BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT
      )
    ) 
    XMLTYPE JOBPAYLOADXML STORE AS SECUREFILE CLOB 
    ( 
        STORAGE ( 
            PCTINCREASE 0 
            MINEXTENTS 1 
            MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED 
            FREELISTS 1 
            BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT 
        ) 
        NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
    ) 
    LOB ("JOBATTACHMENTS") STORE AS SECUREFILE
    (
      NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
      STORAGE(
         MINEXTENTS 1 
         MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
         PCTINCREASE 0 
         FREELISTS 1 
         FREELIST GROUPS 1 
         BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT
      )
    )
;



COMMENT ON TABLE JOBS IS 'The table for holding the jobs.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBNAME IS 'The job name.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOB_ID IS 'The job unique identifier for the new Jobs table record.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBPRIORITY IS 'The pick list value for the assigned job priority which affects the order of processing.  Jobs with lower values are processed first.  Examples: 0=immediate/highest priority, 10=normal/regular prority, 20=lowest priority.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBSTATUS IS 'The overall processing status of the job as it is being processed through the system.  Only override it if you want to place this job on hold.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBUNIQUE_ID IS 'A unique identifier string that can be used by an application to identify the job.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBPRTLOGNAME IS 'The logical printer name to send the job to.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBPAYLOADTYPE IS 'The payload type pick list: 0=XML in JobPayloadXml, 1=JobRequest based XML in JobPayloadXml, 2=Flat file data in JobPayloadBlob, 3=Stacked XML in JobPayloadBlob, 4=Legacy Job based XML, 5=URI reference.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBPAYLOADREF IS 'The payload data reference when the JobPayloadType column value is five (5) - an external reference to a file URI.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBPAYLOADBLOB IS 'The payload data when the JobPayloadType column value is two (2) or three (3) - can contain XML data if the database does not support the XML data type.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBPAYLOADXML IS 'The payload data when JobPayLoadType column value is zero (0), one (1), or four(4).' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBATTACHMENTS IS 'The storage location for the extract data for the transactions of the job.  It contains a serialized and zipped Java hash map of byte arrays that hold the extract data for each transaction in the job.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBSTARTTIME IS 'The date and time when the job was created.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBENDTIME IS 'The date and time when the job completed processing through the system.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBERR_ID IS 'The last error Id found while processing the job through the system.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBTRNTOTAL IS 'The total number of transactions for the job.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBTRNWIP IS 'The number of transactions for the job that were set to manual work in progress status and are awaiting end user input.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBTRNERR IS 'The number of transactions for the job that encountered errors while processing through the system.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBTRNSCH IS 'The number of transactions for the job that were scheduled due to one or more scheduled batches configured in the Bchings table.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBTRNPROC IS 'The number of transactions for the job that were successfully processed to completion through the system.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBTRNSTARTTIME IS 'The date and time when the job transactions began processing.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBTRNENDTIME IS 'The date and time when the job transactions finished processing.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBRCPTOTAL IS 'The total number of recipients for the job.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBRCPERR IS 'The number of recipients for the job that encountered errors during processing.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBRCPSCH IS 'The number of recipients for the job that were scheduled due to one or more scheduled batches configured in the Bchings table.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBRCPPROC IS 'The number of recipients for the job that were successfully processed to completion.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBRCPSTARTTIME IS 'The date and time when the job recipients began processing.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBRCPENDTIME IS 'The date and time when the job recipients finished processing.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBBCHTOTAL IS 'The total number of batches for a job.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBBCHERR IS 'The number of batches for the job that encountered errors while processing.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBBCHSCH IS 'The number of batches for the job that were scheduled due to configuration settings in the Bchings table.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBBCHPROC IS 'The number of batches for the job that were successfully processed to completion.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBBCHSTARTTIME IS 'The date and time when the job batches started processing.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBBCHENDTIME IS 'The date and time when the job batches finished processing.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBRETENTION IS 'The date and time for job retention.  Jobs that have a value that is less than the current system time qualify to be purged from the system.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBRETHOLD IS 'A numerical value of zero (0) or one (1), where one (1) means true, used to indicate if the retention of the job can be extended past the time specified in the JobRetention column.  The default is zero (0).'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBHISTORY IS 'A numerical value of zero (0) or one (1), where one (1) means true, used to indicate if the job table data should be copied to the history table upon deletion.  Can be set to zero (0) by an application before deletion.  The default is one (1).' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBHISTORICAL IS 'A numerical value of zero (0) or one (1), where one (1) means true, used to indicate the job is in the job history table.  The default is zero (0).' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBREPLYTOURI IS 'A reply to URI where the response will be sent once a job is complete.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBREPLYSENT IS 'A numerical value of zero (0) or one (1), where one (1) means true, used to indicate if the reply was sent to the URI specified in the JOBREPLYTOURI column.  The default is zero (0).' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN JOBS.JOBREPLYSENTTIME IS 'A date and time indicating when the reply was sent to the URI specified in the JOBREPLYTOURI column.' 
;
CREATE INDEX JOBS_STATUS ON JOBS 
    ( 
     JOBSTATUS ASC 
    ) 
;
CREATE INDEX JOBS_BREAKDOWN_ANALYTIC ON JOBS 
    ( 
     JOBSTARTTIME ASC , 
     JOBSTATUS ASC 
    ) 
;
CREATE INDEX JOBS_PRIORITY ON JOBS 
    ( 
     JOBPRIORITY ASC , 
     JOBSTATUS ASC 
    ) 
;

ALTER TABLE JOBS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT JOBS_PK PRIMARY KEY ( JOB_ID ) ;

ALTER TABLE JOBS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT JOBS_UNIQUE_ID UNIQUE ( JOBUNIQUE_ID ) 
;


CREATE TABLE JOBSHIST 
    ( 
     JOB_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     JOBNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     JOBPRIORITY NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 10  NOT NULL , 
     JOBSTATUS NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 0  NOT NULL , 
     JOBUNIQUE_ID NVARCHAR2 (47) , 
     JOBPRTLOGNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     JOBPAYLOADTYPE NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 0  NOT NULL , 
     JOBPAYLOADREF NVARCHAR2 (512) , 
     JOBPAYLOADBLOB BLOB , 
     JOBPAYLOADXML XMLTYPE , 
     JOBATTACHMENTS BLOB , 
     JOBSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBERR_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBTRNTOTAL NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBTRNWIP NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBTRNERR NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBTRNSCH NUMBER (38) ,
     JOBTRNPROC NUMBER (38) ,
     JOBTRNSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBTRNENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBRCPTOTAL NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBRCPERR NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBRCPSCH NUMBER (38) ,
     JOBRCPPROC NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBRCPSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBRCPENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBBCHTOTAL NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBBCHERR NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBBCHSCH NUMBER (38) ,
     JOBBCHPROC NUMBER (38) , 
     JOBBCHSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBBCHENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBRETENTION TIMESTAMP , 
     JOBRETHOLD NUMBER (5) , 
     JOBHISTORY NUMBER (5) , 
     JOBHISTORICAL NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 1,
     JOBREPLYTOURI NVARCHAR2 (512) ,
     JOBREPLYSENT NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0 ,
     JOBREPLYSENTTIME TIMESTAMP  
    ) 
    LOB ("JOBPAYLOADBLOB") STORE AS SECUREFILE
    (
      NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS HIGH DEDUPLICATE
      STORAGE(
          MINEXTENTS 1 
          MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
          PCTINCREASE 0 
          FREELISTS 1 
          FREELIST GROUPS 1 
          BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT
      )
    ) 
    XMLTYPE JOBPAYLOADXML STORE AS SECUREFILE CLOB 
    ( 
        STORAGE ( 
            PCTINCREASE 0 
            MINEXTENTS 1 
            MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED 
            FREELISTS 1 
            BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT 
        ) 
        NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS HIGH DEDUPLICATE
    ) 
    LOB ("JOBATTACHMENTS") STORE AS SECUREFILE
    (
      NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS HIGH DEDUPLICATE
      STORAGE(
         MINEXTENTS 1 
         MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
         PCTINCREASE 0 
         FREELISTS 1 
         FREELIST GROUPS 1 
         BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT
      )
    )
;



COMMENT ON TABLE JOBSHIST IS 'History table jobs and status and statistical data. '
;
CREATE INDEX JOBSHIST_STATUS ON JOBSHIST 
    ( 
     JOBSTATUS ASC 
    ) 
;
CREATE INDEX JOBSHIST_BREAKDOWN_ANALYTIC ON JOBSHIST 
    ( 
     JOBSTARTTIME ASC , 
     JOBSTATUS ASC 
    ) 
;
CREATE INDEX JOBSHIST_PRIORITY ON JOBSHIST 
    ( 
     JOBPRIORITY ASC , 
     JOBSTATUS ASC 
    ) 
;

ALTER TABLE JOBSHIST 
    ADD CONSTRAINT JOBSHIST_PK PRIMARY KEY ( JOB_ID ) ;

ALTER TABLE JOBSHIST 
    ADD CONSTRAINT JOBSHIST_UNIQUE_ID UNIQUE ( JOBUNIQUE_ID ) 
;


CREATE TABLE LOCKS 
    ( 
     LOCKNAME NVARCHAR2 (256)  NOT NULL , 
     LOCKED NUMBER (5) , 
     LASTUPDATETIME TIMESTAMP 
    ) 
;
ALTER TABLE LOCKS STORAGE(BUFFER_POOL KEEP);


COMMENT ON TABLE LOCKS IS 'Locks table used to synchronize data locks'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN LOCKS.LOCKED IS 'Locked Boolean, 0 or Null for FALSE.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN LOCKS.LASTUPDATETIME IS 'Last time the Lock was updated' 
;

ALTER TABLE LOCKS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT LOCKS_PK PRIMARY KEY ( LOCKNAME ) ;


CREATE TABLE LOGS 
    ( 
     LOG_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     JOB_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     TRN_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     BCH_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     RCP_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     PUB_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     LOG_CODE NVARCHAR2 (15) , 
     LOGCODE1 NVARCHAR2 (10) , 
     LOGCODE2 NVARCHAR2 (10) , 
     LOGAREA NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     LOGDATA NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     LOGMESSAGE NVARCHAR2 (2000) , 
     LOGTIME TIMESTAMP  NOT NULL , 
     LOGHOSTNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     LOGPROGRAM NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     LOGVERSION NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     LOGMODULE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     LOGPROCESS_ID NVARCHAR2 (10) , 
     LOGTHREAD_ID NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     LOGCATEGORY NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     LOGTAG_ID NVARCHAR2 (256) 
    ) 
;



COMMENT ON TABLE LOGS IS 'Table to log tracing, debugging, auditing'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN LOGS.LOG_ID IS 'Unique auto generated log row identifier' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN LOGS.JOB_ID IS 'JOB_ID foreign key when logging is related to the JOBS row' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN LOGS.TRN_ID IS 'TRN_ID foreign key when logging is related to the TRNS row' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN LOGS.BCH_ID IS 'BCH_ID foreign key when logging is related to the BCHS row' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN LOGS.RCP_ID IS 'RCP_ID foreign key when logging is related to the RCPS row' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN LOGS.LOGPROCESS_ID IS 'Process Id of the error logger' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN LOGS.LOGTAG_ID IS 'Used to tag and follow log entries for a application or a workflow' 
;

ALTER TABLE LOGS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT LOGS_PK PRIMARY KEY ( LOG_ID ) ;


CREATE TABLE PRTLOGICS 
    ( 
     PRTLOG_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     PRTLOGNAME NVARCHAR2 (256)  NOT NULL , 
     PRTLOGSTATUS NUMBER (10) , 
     PRTLOGSTATUSTIME TIMESTAMP ,
     PRTLOGACTIVE NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 1  
    ) 
;



COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTLOGICS.PRTLOG_ID IS 'auto generated surrogate Unique ID for this Logical Printer' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTLOGICS.PRTLOGNAME IS 'The name this logical printer should be referenced by' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTLOGICS.PRTLOGSTATUS IS 'Last known status of this printer, which can be updated by any physical printer that is referenced by this logical printer' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTLOGICS.PRTLOGSTATUSTIME IS 'Represents when the last time the status was updated. This column can be compared to the status time of physical printers to help determine whether or not a physical printer should check the status of itself since last update.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTLOGICS.PRTLOGACTIVE IS 'Logical Printer is Active' 
;

ALTER TABLE PRTLOGICS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT PK_PRTLOGICS PRIMARY KEY ( PRTLOG_ID ) ;

ALTER TABLE PRTLOGICS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT PRTLOGICS_PRTLOGNAME UNIQUE ( PRTLOGNAME ) 
;


CREATE TABLE PRTPHYCFGS 
    ( 
     PRTPHY_ID NUMBER (38) NOT NULL , 
     PRTPHYCFG_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     PRTPHYCFGPROPERTY NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PRTPHYCFGVALUE NVARCHAR2 (256) ,
     PRTPHYCFGACTIVE NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 1  
    ) 
;



COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYCFGS.PRTPHYCFG_ID IS 'Unique ID for this printer configuration property' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYCFGS.PRTPHYCFGPROPERTY IS 'The property of this configuration item. The property name is used to determine how this configuration item will modify the printer' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYCFGS.PRTPHYCFGVALUE IS 'The value of this configuration property' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYCFGS.PRTPHYCFGACTIVE IS 'Physical Printer Configuration is Active' 
;

ALTER TABLE PRTPHYCFGS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT PK_PRTPHYCFG PRIMARY KEY ( PRTPHYCFG_ID ) ;


CREATE TABLE PRTPHYS 
    ( 
     PRTLOG_ID NUMBER (38) NOT NULL , 
     PRTPHY_ID NUMBER (38) NOT NULL , 
     PRTPHYSEQ NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 1, 
     PRTPHYNODE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PRTPHYNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PRTPHYSTATUS NUMBER (10) , 
     PRTPHYSTATUSTIME TIMESTAMP ,
     PRTPHYACTIVE NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 1  
    ) 
;


COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYS.PRTPHY_ID IS 'Physical printer unique ID that this configuration property relates to' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYS.PRTPHYSEQ IS 'Prefered order for selection' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYS.PRTPHYNODE IS 'Host Node name  the physical printer is defined on.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYS.PRTPHYNAME IS 'Name of the printer installed on the related node referenced in the PHYPRTNODE column. The name matches exactly as it appears installed on the node.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYS.PRTPHYSTATUS IS 'The status of this printer as last updated by the associated PRTPHYNODE.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYS.PRTPHYSTATUSTIME IS 'Date time of last status from physical printer' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PRTPHYS.PRTPHYACTIVE IS 'Physical Printer is Active' 
;

ALTER TABLE PRTPHYS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT PK_PRTPHYS PRIMARY KEY ( PRTPHY_ID ) ;


CREATE TABLE PUBNTFS 
    ( 
     PUBNTFMSGTYP NVARCHAR2 (50)  NOT NULL , 
     PUBNTFLANG NVARCHAR2 (20)  NOT NULL , 
     PUBNTFSUBJ NVARCHAR2 (50) , 
     PUBNTFTXT NVARCHAR2 (2000) , 
     PUBNTFHTML BLOB , 
     PUBNTFSPEECH NVARCHAR2 (2000) 
    ) 
    LOB ("PUBNTFHTML") STORE AS SECUREFILE
    (
      NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
      STORAGE(
          MINEXTENTS 1 
          MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
          PCTINCREASE 0 
          FREELISTS 1 
          FREELIST GROUPS 1 
          BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT
      )
    ) 
;



COMMENT ON TABLE PUBNTFS IS 'Publication Notification Setup Table'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBNTFS.PUBNTFMSGTYP IS 'Publication Notification Message Type key.  Allows mapping a message template
to data elements.  Publication Notifier has configuration to allow ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBNTFS.PUBNTFLANG IS 'Language of the template, used to select the appropriate language of the 
recipient of the message, defaults to en for English of appropriate 
language can not be found.  ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBNTFS.PUBNTFSUBJ IS 'Subject line template for email notifications' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBNTFS.PUBNTFTXT IS 'Simple text template for SMS or text email' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBNTFS.PUBNTFHTML IS 'HTML format of a notification for MMS or HTML emails' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBNTFS.PUBNTFSPEECH IS 'Text to Speech for notifications.' 
;

ALTER TABLE PUBNTFS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT PUBNTFS_PK PRIMARY KEY ( PUBNTFLANG, PUBNTFMSGTYP ) ;


CREATE TABLE PUBS 
    ( 
     BCH_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     PUB_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     PUBBEGINRCP_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     PUBENDRCP_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     PUBUNIQUE_ID NVARCHAR2 (47)  NOT NULL , 
     PUBNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PUBSEQ NUMBER (10) , 
     PUBPRTTYPE NVARCHAR2 (30) , 
     PUBPRTEXT NVARCHAR2 (6) , 
     PUBSTATUS NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 490 , 
     PUBSIGNOFF NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PUBSIGNOFFTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     PUBDATATYPE NVARCHAR2 (30) , 
     PUBOUTTYPE NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBOUTBLOB BLOB , 
     PUBOUTREF NVARCHAR2 (512) , 
     PUBOUTSIZE NUMBER (20) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     PUBENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     PUBTRNCOUNT NUMBER (38) , 
     PUBRCPCOUNT NUMBER (38) , 
     PUBPAGECOUNT NUMBER (38) , 
     PUBSHEETCOUNT NUMBER (38) , 
     PUBWEIGHT NUMBER (19,4) , 
     PUBTRAY1 NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBTRAY1DESC NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     PUBTRAY2 NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBTRAY2DESC NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     PUBTRAY3 NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBTRAY3DESC NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     PUBTRAY4 NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBTRAY4DESC NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     PUBTRAY5 NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBTRAY5DESC NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     PUBTRAY6 NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBTRAY6DESC NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     PUBTRAY7 NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBTRAY7DESC NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     PUBTRAY8 NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBTRAY8DESC NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     PUBTRAY9 NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBTRAY9DESC NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     PUBERR_ID NUMBER (38) , 
     PUBARCHIVED NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBARCDOCTYPE NVARCHAR2 (30) , 
     PUBARCDOCSUBTYPE NVARCHAR2 (30) , 
     PUBARCDOCNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PUBARCREF NVARCHAR2 (512) , 
     PUBARCTITLE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PUBARCSTATUS NUMBER (10) , 
     PUBARCSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     PUBARCENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     PUBSIGNED NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBSGNDOCTYPE NVARCHAR2 (30) , 
     PUBSGNDOCSUBTYPE NVARCHAR2 (30) , 
     PUBSGNDOCNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PUBSGNREF NVARCHAR2 (512) , 
     PUBSGNTITLE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PUBSGNSTATUS NUMBER (10) , 
     PUBSGNSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     PUBSGNENDTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     PUBPUBLISHED NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0 , 
     PUBMIMETYPE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PUBPRTLOGNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PUBPRTPHYNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     PUBPUBSTATUS NUMBER (5) , 
     PUBPUBSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP , 
     PUBPUBENDTIME TIMESTAMP ,

     PUBHISTORICAL NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0

      NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
      STORAGE(
          MINEXTENTS 1 
          MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
          PCTINCREASE 0

      )
    )

COMMENT ON TABLE PUBS IS 'Publications for distribution to print, email, etc. and for notifications.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUB_ID IS 'Publication Record ID' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBBEGINRCP_ID IS 'Starting RCP_ID for the print which allows for identifying columns such as address information that starts a print stream' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBENDRCP_ID IS 'Ending RCP_ID for the print which allows for identifying columns such as address information that starts a print stream.
If the PUBBEGINRCP_ID = PUBENDREC_ID or PUBENDRCP_ID=null then this is output is only for one recipient
' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBUNIQUE_ID IS 'Unique GUID for application lookup' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBNAME IS 'Publication Name' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBPRTTYPE IS 'Output Type for the Batch (PDF, PS, AFP, XER, TXT, HTML, VPP, ...)' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBPRTEXT IS 'Printer extension for file.  Configured in Presenter related to Documaker 
PRTTYPE configuration group and output during print stream data generation. 
Needed because some ECM systems need a proper file extension like pdf, ps, met, rtf, pcl, etc 
that is different than Documakers PRTTYPE definitions and they don''t except 
mimetypes we specify by BCHINGS configuration.   ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBSTATUS IS 'Status of the PUBS record.  Relates to JobStatus.
511=ready for archiving (ready for archiver)
521=sent to archiver
541=processing error
590=processing success
611=ready for publishing/printing (ready for publisher printing).
621=ready for publishing
641=processing error
690=processing success
711=ready for publication notification (ready for publisher notifing).
721=ready for publishing
741=processing error
790=processing success' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBSIGNOFF IS 'Name of the person or processes who signed off on the print and/or distribution completed successfully,
e.g. the print was completed and mail was delivered to the post office. 
This is for Finishing Requirements.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBSIGNOFFTIME IS 'When the signoff occurred' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBDATATYPE IS 'Detail of the actual type of output data, 
e.g. PDF, PCL, XER, AFP, XML, TXT, EMAIL' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBOUTTYPE IS 'Identifies which PUBOUT column contains the date type for the output:
0=BLOB (default)
1=File/URL Reference
The data generally is print stream specific so it can be binary. ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBOUTBLOB IS 'When PUBOUTTYPE is a BLOB this type is populated with 
the content directly' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBOUTREF IS 'When PUBOUTTYPE is a file reference this type is populated with 
a fully qualified URL or UNC or file reference' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBOUTSIZE IS 'The publication data size.' ;


COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBSTARTTIME IS 'When this print record started processing, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBENDTIME IS 'When this print record processing was completed, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBTRNCOUNT IS 'Total number of transactions in the output.  Statistical.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBRCPCOUNT IS 'Total number of rcps in the output.  Statistical.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBPAGECOUNT IS 'Total Page Count for this print output, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBSHEETCOUNT IS 'Total Sheet Count for this print output, statistical' 
;
COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBTRAY1 IS 'Tray 1 Sheet Count'; 
COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBTRAY1DESC IS 'Tray 1 Description';

for storage of document' 
;

for storage of document'

;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBSGNDOCTYPE IS 'Signed Document Type, used as classification for signing document'

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBSGNDOCSUBTYPE IS 'Signed SubDocument Type, used as classification for signing of document'

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBHISTORY IS '1 True by default.  
Indicates if the pubs table data is to be copied to the history table upon delete.  
Is set to 0 False by an application before deleting if a purge is needed. ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN PUBS.PUBHISTORICAL IS 'Indicator that PUB is in the HISTORY table.
Defaults to FALSE (0) and when inserted into the PUBSHIST defaults to 
TRUE (1).  Must be reset to FALSE (0) if data is taken from thei History 
and reprocessed in the active tables. ' 
;
CREATE INDEX PUBS_STATS ON PUBS 
    ( 
     PUBSTATUS ASC 
    ) 
;
CREATE INDEX PUBS_PUBNOTIFIED ON PUBS 
    ( 
     PUBNOTIFIED ASC 
    ) 
;
CREATE INDEX PUBS_PUBPUBLISHED ON PUBS 
    ( 
     PUBPUBLISHED ASC 
    ) 
;
CREATE INDEX PUBS_PUBARCHIVED ON PUBS 
    ( 
     PUBARCHIVED ASC 
    ) 
;
CREATE INDEX PUBS_SEQ ON PUBS 
    ( 
     BCH_ID ASC , 
     PUBSEQ ASC 
    ) 
;
CREATE INDEX PUBS_BCH_ID ON PUBS 
    ( 
     BCH_ID ASC 
    ) 
;

ALTER TABLE PUBS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT PUB_PK PRIMARY KEY ( PUB_ID, BCH_ID ) ;

ALTER TABLE PUBS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT PUBUNIQUE_ID UNIQUE ( PUBUNIQUE_ID ) 
;

    )

CREATE TABLE RCPS 
    ( 
     RCP_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     TRN_ID NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     RCPUNIQUE_ID NVARCHAR2 (47)  NOT NULL , 
     BATCHNAME NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     BATCHTYPE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPSTATUS NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 411 , 
     RCPBCHTOTAL NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     RCPBCHERR NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 , 
     RCPBCHPROC NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0 ,
     RCPBCHSCH NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0,
     RCPDATATYPE NVARCHAR2 (30) , 
     RCPOUTTYPE NUMBER (10) DEFAULT 0 , 
     RCPOUTBLOB BLOB , 
     RCPOUTREF NVARCHAR2 (512) , 
     RCPOUTSIZE NUMBER (20) DEFAULT 0,
     RCPSTARTTIME TIMESTAMP ,

     ADR_INDEX NVARCHAR2 (10) ,

     ADR_NAME2 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ADR_ADDRESS1 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ADR_ADDRESS2 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ADR_CITY NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ADR_STATE NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ADR_COUNTRY NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ADR_POSTALCODE NVARCHAR2 (20) , 
     ADR_EMAIL NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     ADR_ENCLOSURES NVARCHAR2 (5) , 
     ADR_FAX NVARCHAR2 (20) ,

     RCPAPPDEC002 NUMBER (19,4) ,

     RCPAPPDEC004 NUMBER (19,4) , 
     RCPAPPDEC005 NUMBER (19,4) ,

     RCPAPPINT005 NUMBER (20) ,

     RCPAPPSTR006 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPAPPSTR007 NVARCHAR2 (256) ,

     RCPAPPSTR009 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPAPPSTR010 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPAPPSTR011 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPAPPSTR012 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPAPPSTR013 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPAPPSTR014 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPAPPSTR015 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPCUSDATE001 TIMESTAMP , 
     RCPCUSDATE002 TIMESTAMP , 
     RCPCUSDATE003 TIMESTAMP , 
     RCPCUSDATE004 TIMESTAMP , 
     RCPCUSDATE005 TIMESTAMP , 
     RCPCUSDEC001 NUMBER (19,4) ,

     RCPCUSSTR015 NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCBPRTFLAG NVARCHAR2 (5) , 
     RCBRCPCODE NVARCHAR2 (10) , 
     RCBRCPNAME NVARCHAR2 (100) , 
     RCBERROR NVARCHAR2 (256) , 
     RCPHISTORY NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 1 , 
     RCPHISTORICAL NUMBER (5) DEFAULT 0 
    ) 
    LOB ("RCPOUTBLOB") STORE AS SECUREFILE
    (
      NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
      STORAGE(
          MINEXTENTS 1 
          MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
          PCTINCREASE 0 
          FREELISTS 1 
          FREELIST GROUPS 1 
          BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT
      )
    ) 
;



COMMENT ON TABLE RCPS IS 'Recipient data created from Transactions'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCP_ID IS 'Recipient Record ID' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.TRN_ID IS 'Transaction Identification Foreign Key' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPUNIQUE_ID IS 'Unique GUID for application lookup' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.BATCHTYPE IS 'Further classification of the Batch for the batching rules' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPSTATUS IS 'Status of the RCPS record.  Relates to JobStatus.
Indicator of the status of a RCPS row in relation to processing by the factory ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPBCHTOTAL IS 'Batches that include this Recipient Record.  Set by the batcher when it takes 
the recipent and assignes it to one or more batches' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPBCHERR IS 'Batches that include this Recipient Record with an error.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPBCHPROC IS 'Currently processed batches that recipient is included in.  
Incremented by the Presenter during the procesing of the print.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPDATATYPE IS 'Detail of the actual type of Notification output data, 
e.g. TXT, HTML ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPOUTTYPE IS 'Identifies which RCPOUT column contains the date type for the Notification output: ';

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPOUTBLOB IS 'When RCPOUTTYPE is a BLOB this type is populated with the Notification content directly.  ';

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPOUTREF IS 'When RCPOUTTYPE is a file reference this type is populated with a fully qualified URL or UNC or file reference for the Notification content.' ;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPOUTSIZE IS 'The size of the recipient notification content.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPSTARTTIME IS 'When this recipient record started processing, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPENDTIME IS 'When this recipient record processing was completed, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPPAGECOUNT IS 'Total Page Count for this recipient output, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPSHEETCOUNT IS 'Total Sheet Count for this recipient output, statistical' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPWEIGHT IS 'Calculated weight based on sheet count and stock per tray in NA POL
document data. ' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.RCPTRAY1 IS 'Tray 1 Calcuated Sheet Count';

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.ADR_HOMEPHONE IS 'LandLine Phone number.  Useful for sending automated text to speach messages
from UMS as an alternative when a SMS can''t be sent because no mobile 
phone listed.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN RCPS.ADR_PREFERRED IS 'Prefered Distribution. 
Hex for bitmask values used internally to enable any combination of these 
options: 
 0=(Hex 0) None   
 1=(Hex 1) BATCH 
 2=(Hex 2) LOCAL
 4=(Hex 4) EMAIL
 8=(Hex 8) MMS
16=(Hex 10) SMS
32=(Hex 20) FAX' 
;

TRUE (1).  Must be reset to FALSE (0) if data is taken from thei History 
and reprocessed in the active tables. '

    (

    (

    (

    ADD CONSTRAINT TRANSTATUSCODES_PK PRIMARY KEY ( STRCODEID ) ;


CREATE TABLE TRNS 
    ( 
     JOB_ID NUMBER (38) DEFAULT 0  NOT NULL ,

    ( 
        STORAGE ( 
            PCTINCREASE 0 
            MINEXTENTS 1 
            MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED 
            FREELISTS 1 
            BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT 
        ) 
        NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
    ) 
    LOB ("TRNDATABLOB") STORE AS SECUREFILE
    (
      NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
      STORAGE(
          MINEXTENTS 1 
          MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
          PCTINCREASE 0 
          FREELISTS 1 
          FREELIST GROUPS 1 
          BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT
      )
    ) 
    XMLTYPE TRNNAPOLXML STORE AS SECUREFILE CLOB 
    ( 
        STORAGE ( 
            PCTINCREASE 0 
            MINEXTENTS 1 
            MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED 
            FREELISTS 1 
            BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT 
        ) 
        NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
    ) 
    LOB ("TRNNAPOLBLOB") STORE AS SECUREFILE
    (
      NOCACHE FILESYSTEM_LIKE_LOGGING COMPRESS DEDUPLICATE
      STORAGE(
          MINEXTENTS 1 
          MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
          PCTINCREASE 0 
          FREELISTS 1 
          FREELIST GROUPS 1 
          BUFFER_POOL DEFAULT
      )
    ) 
    PARALLEL
;



COMMENT ON TABLE TRNS IS 'Contains the transactions for a job.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.AGENCYID IS 'The agency Id.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.INUSE IS 'The in-use flag.  Only set this value if you wish to lock the transaction.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.JURISDICTN IS 'The transaction jurisdiction code.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.LOCID IS 'The location Id.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.MODIFYTIME IS 'The last date and time the NA/POl was modified.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNMODIFYTIME IS 'The last date and time the transaction was modified.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.PROCESSNAME IS 'The process name that created this transaction - normally set by the application inserting the job but can be overriden if needed.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.QUEUEID IS 'The queue identifier.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.REASON_ID IS 'The reason code for routing rejection or processing.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.RETENTION IS 'A date and time stamp that indicates how long to retain the transaction.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.SECLEVEL IS 'The security level for the transaction.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.SUBLOCID IS 'The sub-location Id.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNENDTIME IS 'The transaction ending date and time.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNERR_ID IS 'The transaction error Id when an error was encountered during processing.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNSTARTTIME IS 'The transaction starting date and time.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.FROMGROUP IS 'The group that assigned the transaction.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.FROMTIME IS 'The date and time the transaction was assigned from a user or group.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.FROMUSER IS 'The user who assigned the transaction.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TOGROUP IS 'The group the transaction was assigned to.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TOTIME IS 'The date and time the transaction was assigned to a user or group.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TOUSER IS 'The user the transaction was assigned to.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.CUSTOMIZED IS 'A numerical flag of zero (0) or one (1), where one (1) means true, used to indicate if the transaction is customized. Reserved for future use.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.ACTION IS 'The action value. Use this columm to override the default value if you have custom actions that should be performed on the transaction by the system.  The default is batch created. '
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.JOB_ID IS 'The unique identifier for the job this transaction belongs to - this is a foreign key to a job in the Jobs table.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRN_ID IS 'The unique identifier for the transaction - this is the primary key for the Trns table.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.UNIQUE_ID IS 'A unique identifier string that can be used for application look up of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.KEY1 IS 'The key 1 value.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.KEY2 IS 'The key 2 value.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.KEY3 IS 'The key 3 value.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.KEYID IS 'The key Id value.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.FORMSETID IS 'The formset unique identifier.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.ARCKEY IS 'The archive key.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.ARCTIME IS 'The archive time.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.BEGINTIME IS 'The date and time the transaction processing began.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.ENDTIME IS 'The date and time the transaction processing ended.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.CREATETIME IS 'The date and time the transaction was created.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.RECTYPE IS 'The record type.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.DESCR IS 'The transaction description.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNNAME IS 'The name of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.DOCTYPE IS 'The document type of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.DOCSUBTYPE IS 'The document sub-type of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.ORIGUSER IS 'The original user or creator / author of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.CURRUSER IS 'The current user of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.CURRGROUP IS 'The group of the current user of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.CURRROLE IS 'The role of the current user of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.CURRSUPER IS 'The supervisor of the current user of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.CURRAPP_ID IS 'The current application owner of the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.STATUSCODE IS 'The status code of the transaction.  The value is set by the system to be either "W", "E", "B", or "P" as part of the Document Factory processing but may be overwritten if provided here.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRANCODE IS 'The transaction code for the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.APPROVALSTATE IS 'The data related to the approval process workflow:  Draft = 10, Pending Approval = 20, Approved = 30, Rejected = 40, Pending Distribution = 50, Distributed = 60.' 
;

;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNSTATUS IS 'A numerical value that indicates the overall status of the transaction as it is being processed through the system.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNRCPTOTAL IS 'The total number of recipients for the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNRCPERR IS 'The number of recipients for the transaction that encountered errors while processing through the system.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNRCPSCH IS 'The number of recipients for the transaction that were scheduled due to one or more of its associated batches being scheduled.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNRCPPROC IS 'The number of recipients for the transaction that were successfully processed to completion by the system.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNBCHTOTAL IS 'The total number of batches for the transaction.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNBCHERR IS 'The number of batches for the transaction that encountered errors while processing through the system.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNBCHSCH IS 'The number of batches for the transaction that were scheduled.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNBCHPROC IS 'The number of batches for the transaction that were successfully processed to completion by the system.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNDATATYPE IS 'The transaction input data type pick list:  0=data in XML data type, 1=data in BLOB, 3=URI reference of XML, 4=URI reference of non-XML.  Used to indicate which column the import data is in.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNDATAREF IS 'The transaction data reference when TrnDataType column value is three (3) or four (4) - an external reference to a file URI.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNDATAXML IS 'The transaction data in XML type when TrnDataType column value is zero (0).' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNDATABLOB IS 'The transaction data in BLOB type when TrnDataType column value is one (1).' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNDATASIZE IS 'The transaction data size.' ;


COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNNAPOLTYPE IS 'The transaction NA and POL data type pick list:  0=data in XML data type TRNNAPOLXML, 1=data in BLOB TRNNAPOLBLOB, 3=URI reference of XML, 4=URI reference of non-XML.  Used to indicate which column the processed NA and POL data is in.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNNAPOLREF IS 'The transaction NA and POL data reference when TrnNaPolType column value is three (3) or four (4) - an external reference to a file URI.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNNAPOLXML IS 'The transaction NA and POL data when TrnNaPolType column value is zero (0).' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNNAPOLBLOB IS 'The transaction NA and POL data when TrnNaPolType column value is one (1).' 
;
COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNNAPOLSIZE IS 'The transation NA and POL data size.' ;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNPRTLOGNAME IS 'The logical printer name when the transaction is sent to a predetermined logical printer.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNRETHOLD IS 'A numerical value of zero (0) or one (1), where one (1) means true, used for overriding the retention date removal.  The default is zero (0).'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNDOLOG IS 'A numerical value of zero (0) or one (1), where one (1) means true, used to control when the TrnsLog table is updated.  The default is zero (0).  Setting this value to one (1) will enable logging for this and future actions on this transaction into the TrnsLog table unless a subsequent process disables logging.'
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNHISTORY IS 'A numerical value of zero (0) or one (1), where one (1) means true, used to control if the Trns table data should be copied to the history table upon deletion.  It can be set to zero (0) by an application before deletion.  The default is one (1).' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.TRNHISTORICAL IS 'A numerical value of zero (0) or one (1), where one (1) means true, used to indicate the transaction is in the TrnsHist history table.' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNS.SRCTRN_ID IS 'The identifier for the transaction - when the transaction is created from a different transaction as a starting point.' 
;

    ( 
     KEY1 ASC 
    ) 
;

    )

     TRNSTATUS ASC

    )

    )

     TRNSTATUS ASC  
    ) 
;

    ( 
     JOB_ID ASC  
    )

    ADD CONSTRAINT TRNS_PK PRIMARY KEY ( TRN_ID ) ;

ALTER TABLE TRNS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT TRNS_UNIQUE_ID UNIQUE ( UNIQUE_ID ) 
;

ALTER TABLE TRNS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT TRNS_FORMSETID UNIQUE ( FORMSETID ) 
;


CREATE TABLE TRNSD 
    ( 
     FORMSETID NVARCHAR2 (47)  NOT NULL , 
     SEQ_NUM NVARCHAR2 (5)  NOT NULL , 
     CONT_FLAG NVARCHAR2 (10)  NOT NULL , 
     TOTAL_SIZE NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL , 
     CARDATA RAW (2000)  NOT NULL 
    ) 
;



COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNSD.FORMSETID IS 'Formset Unique Identifier' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNSD.SEQ_NUM IS 'Sequence Order' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNSD.CONT_FLAG IS 'Continuation Flag' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNSD.TOTAL_SIZE IS 'Total Size of all TRNSD rows for FORMSETID' 
;

COMMENT ON COLUMN TRNSD.CARDATA IS 'Raw compressed package part' 
;

ALTER TABLE TRNSD 
    ADD CONSTRAINT TRNS_PK_1 UNIQUE ( FORMSETID , SEQ_NUM ) 
;

      STORAGE(
          MINEXTENTS 1 
          MAXEXTENTS UNLIMITED
          PCTINCREASE 0

          FREELIST GROUPS 1

      )
    )

    ( 
     CAST(TRNSLOG_ID as NVARCHAR2(47)) ASC  
    ) 
;

    ( 
     KEY1 ASC 
    ) 
;

    ( 
     KEYID ASC 
    ) 
;

    ( 
     KEY1 ASC , 
     KEY2 ASC , 
     KEYID ASC , 
     RECTYPE ASC 
    ) 
;

    ( 
     KEY2 ASC 
    )

    ( 
     CURRUSER ASC 
    ) 
;

    ( 
     JOB_ID ASC  
    ) 
;

    ( 
     TRN_ID ASC  
    ) 
;

CREATE INDEX "TRNSLOG_RECTYPE" ON "TRNSLOG" (RECTYPE);
CREATE INDEX "TRNSLOG_DOCTYPE" ON "TRNSLOG" (DOCTYPE);
CREATE INDEX "TRNSLOG_DOCSUBTYPE" ON "TRNSLOG" (DOCSUBTYPE);
CREATE INDEX "TRNSLOG_UNIQUE_ID" ON "TRNSLOG" (UNIQUE_ID);
CREATE INDEX "TRNSLOG_UPUNIQUEID" ON "TRNSLOG" (UPPER(UNIQUE_ID));



ALTER TABLE PUBS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT BCHS_PUB FOREIGN KEY 
    ( 
     BCH_ID
    ) 
    REFERENCES BCHS 
    ( 
     BCH_ID
    ) 
;


ALTER TABLE BCHS_RCPS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT FK_ASS_2 FOREIGN KEY 
    ( 
     BCH_ID
    ) 
    REFERENCES BCHS 
    ( 
     BCH_ID
    ) 
;


ALTER TABLE BCHS_RCPS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT FK_ASS_3 FOREIGN KEY 
    ( 
     RCP_ID,
     TRN_ID
    ) 
    REFERENCES RCPS 
    ( 
     RCP_ID,
     TRN_ID
    ) 
;


 ALTER TABLE TRNS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT JOBS_TRNS FOREIGN KEY 
    ( 
     JOB_ID
    ) 
    REFERENCES JOBS 
    ( 
     JOB_ID
    ) 
;


ALTER TABLE PRTPHYS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT PRTLOGICS_PRTPHYS FOREIGN KEY 
    ( 
     PRTLOG_ID
    ) 
    REFERENCES PRTLOGICS 
    ( 
     PRTLOG_ID
    ) 
    ON DELETE CASCADE 
;


ALTER TABLE PRTPHYCFGS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT PRTPHYS_PRTPHYCFGS FOREIGN KEY 
    ( 
     PRTPHY_ID
    ) 
    REFERENCES PRTPHYS 
    ( 
     PRTPHY_ID
    ) 
    ON DELETE CASCADE 
;


ALTER TABLE RCPS 
    ADD CONSTRAINT TRNS_RCPS FOREIGN KEY 
    ( 
     TRN_ID
    ) 
    REFERENCES TRNS 
    ( 
     TRN_ID
    ) 
;

CREATE TABLE TAGS ( 
   TAG_ID        NUMBER (38)  NOT NULL,
   TAGTYPE       NVARCHAR2 (10) NOT NULL,
   TAGVALUE      NVARCHAR2 (30) NOT NULL,
   TAGENTITYID   NUMBER (38),
   TAGCREATETIME TIMESTAMP , 
   PRIMARY KEY (TAGTYPE, TAG_ID, TAGVALUE)
);

COMMENT ON COLUMN TAGS.TAG_ID IS 'Tag Unique Identifier' ;
COMMENT ON COLUMN TAGS.TAGTYPE IS 'Tag related Object Type' ;
COMMENT ON COLUMN TAGS.TAGVALUE IS 'User assigned value for searching for tag' ;
COMMENT ON COLUMN TAGS.TAGENTITYID IS 'User that created the tag' ;
COMMENT ON COLUMN TAGS.TAGCREATETIME IS 'UTC time for when the Tag was created' ;

CREATE INDEX TAGS_TAGVALUES ON TAGS
    ( 
     TAGENTITYID ASC 
    ) 
;


CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW BCHSALL AS
SELECT * FROM BCHS UNION ALL SELECT * FROM BCHSHIST ;

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW BCHS_RCPSALL AS
SELECT * FROM BCHS_RCPS UNION ALL SELECT * FROM BCHS_RCPSHIST ;

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW JOBSALL AS
SELECT * FROM JOBS UNION ALL SELECT * FROM JOBSHIST ;

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW PUBSALL AS
SELECT * FROM PUBS UNION ALL SELECT * FROM PUBSHIST ;

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW RCPSALL AS
SELECT * FROM RCPS UNION ALL SELECT * FROM RCPSHIST ;

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW TRNSALL AS
SELECT * FROM TRNS UNION ALL SELECT * FROM TRNSHIST ;

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW TRNSSNAPSHOT AS
SELECT 0 AS TRNSLOG_ID,JOB_ID, TRN_ID, UNIQUE_ID, KEY1, KEY2, KEY3, KEYID, FORMSETID, ARCKEY, RECTYPE, DESCR, TRNNAME, DOCTYPE, DOCSUBTYPE, ORIGUSER, CURRUSER, CURRGROUP, CURRROLE, CURRSUPER, CURRAPP_ID, STATUSCODE, TRANCODE , APPROVALSTATE, SECLEVEL, TRNERR_ID, INUSE, CUSTOMIZED, CREATETIME, BEGINTIME, TRNSTARTTIME, MODIFYTIME, TRNMODIFYTIME, ARCTIME, RETENTION, TRNENDTIME, ENDTIME, APPDATA, JURISDICTN, LOCID, QUEUEID, SUBLOCID, AGENCYID, FROMUSER, FROMTIME, FROMGROUP, TOTIME, TOUSER, TOGROUP, ROUTEDESC, PROCESSNAME, TRNAPPDATE001, TRNAPPDATE002, TRNAPPDATE003, TRNAPPDATE004, TRNAPPDATE005, TRNAPPDEC001, TRNAPPDEC002, TRNAPPDEC003, TRNAPPDEC004, TRNAPPDEC005, TRNAPPINT001, TRNAPPINT002, TRNAPPINT003, TRNAPPINT004, TRNAPPINT005, TRNAPPSTR001, TRNAPPSTR002, TRNAPPSTR003, TRNAPPSTR004, TRNAPPSTR005, TRNAPPSTR006, TRNAPPSTR007, TRNAPPSTR008, TRNAPPSTR009, TRNAPPSTR010, TRNAPPSTR011, TRNAPPSTR012, TRNAPPSTR013, TRNAPPSTR014, TRNAPPSTR015, TRNCUSDATE001, TRNCUSDATE002, TRNCUSDATE003, TRNCUSDATE004, TRNCUSDATE005, TRNCUSDATE006, TRNCUSDATE007, TRNCUSDATE008, TRNCUSDATE009, TRNCUSDATE010, TRNCUSDATE011, TRNCUSDATE012, TRNCUSDATE013, TRNCUSDATE014, TRNCUSDATE015, TRNCUSDEC001, TRNCUSDEC002, TRNCUSDEC003, TRNCUSDEC004, TRNCUSDEC005, TRNCUSINT001, TRNCUSINT002, TRNCUSINT003, TRNCUSINT004, TRNCUSINT005, TRNCUSSTR001, TRNCUSSTR002, TRNCUSSTR003, TRNCUSSTR004, TRNCUSSTR005, TRNCUSSTR006, TRNCUSSTR007, TRNCUSSTR008, TRNCUSSTR009, TRNCUSSTR010, TRNCUSSTR011, TRNCUSSTR012, TRNCUSSTR013, TRNCUSSTR014, TRNCUSSTR015, TRNCUSSTR016, TRNCUSSTR017, TRNCUSSTR018, TRNCUSSTR019, TRNCUSSTR020, ACTION, REASON_ID, TRNSTATUS, TRNRCPTOTAL, TRNRCPERR, TRNRCPSCH, TRNRCPPROC, TRNBCHTOTAL, TRNBCHERR, TRNBCHSCH, TRNBCHPROC, TRNDATATYPE, TRNDATAREF, TRNDATAXML, TRNDATABLOB, TRNDATASIZE, TRNNAPOLTYPE, TRNNAPOLREF, TRNNAPOLXML, TRNNAPOLBLOB, TRNNAPOLSIZE, TRNPRTLOGNAME, TRNDOLOG, TRNRETHOLD, TRNHISTORY, TRNHISTORICAL, SRCTRN_ID FROM TRNS 
UNION ALL SELECT 0 AS TRNSLOG_ID,JOB_ID, TRN_ID, UNIQUE_ID, KEY1, KEY2, KEY3, KEYID, FORMSETID, ARCKEY, RECTYPE, DESCR, TRNNAME, DOCTYPE, DOCSUBTYPE, ORIGUSER, CURRUSER, CURRGROUP, CURRROLE, CURRSUPER, CURRAPP_ID, STATUSCODE, TRANCODE , APPROVALSTATE, SECLEVEL, TRNERR_ID, INUSE, CUSTOMIZED, CREATETIME, BEGINTIME, TRNSTARTTIME, MODIFYTIME, TRNMODIFYTIME, ARCTIME, RETENTION, TRNENDTIME, ENDTIME, APPDATA, JURISDICTN, LOCID, QUEUEID, SUBLOCID, AGENCYID, FROMUSER, FROMTIME, FROMGROUP, TOTIME, TOUSER, TOGROUP, ROUTEDESC, PROCESSNAME, TRNAPPDATE001, TRNAPPDATE002, TRNAPPDATE003, TRNAPPDATE004, TRNAPPDATE005, TRNAPPDEC001, TRNAPPDEC002, TRNAPPDEC003, TRNAPPDEC004, TRNAPPDEC005, TRNAPPINT001, TRNAPPINT002, TRNAPPINT003, TRNAPPINT004, TRNAPPINT005, TRNAPPSTR001, TRNAPPSTR002, TRNAPPSTR003, TRNAPPSTR004, TRNAPPSTR005, TRNAPPSTR006, TRNAPPSTR007, TRNAPPSTR008, TRNAPPSTR009, TRNAPPSTR010, TRNAPPSTR011, TRNAPPSTR012, TRNAPPSTR013, TRNAPPSTR014, TRNAPPSTR015, TRNCUSDATE001, TRNCUSDATE002, TRNCUSDATE003, TRNCUSDATE004, TRNCUSDATE005, TRNCUSDATE006, TRNCUSDATE007, TRNCUSDATE008, TRNCUSDATE009, TRNCUSDATE010, TRNCUSDATE011, TRNCUSDATE012, TRNCUSDATE013, TRNCUSDATE014, TRNCUSDATE015, TRNCUSDEC001, TRNCUSDEC002, TRNCUSDEC003, TRNCUSDEC004, TRNCUSDEC005, TRNCUSINT001, TRNCUSINT002, TRNCUSINT003, TRNCUSINT004, TRNCUSINT005, TRNCUSSTR001, TRNCUSSTR002, TRNCUSSTR003, TRNCUSSTR004, TRNCUSSTR005, TRNCUSSTR006, TRNCUSSTR007, TRNCUSSTR008, TRNCUSSTR009, TRNCUSSTR010, TRNCUSSTR011, TRNCUSSTR012, TRNCUSSTR013, TRNCUSSTR014, TRNCUSSTR015, TRNCUSSTR016, TRNCUSSTR017, TRNCUSSTR018, TRNCUSSTR019, TRNCUSSTR020, ACTION, REASON_ID, TRNSTATUS, TRNRCPTOTAL, TRNRCPERR, TRNRCPSCH, TRNRCPPROC, TRNBCHTOTAL, TRNBCHERR, TRNBCHSCH, TRNBCHPROC, TRNDATATYPE, TRNDATAREF, TRNDATAXML, TRNDATABLOB, TRNDATASIZE, TRNNAPOLTYPE, TRNNAPOLREF, TRNNAPOLXML, TRNNAPOLBLOB, TRNNAPOLSIZE, TRNPRTLOGNAME, TRNDOLOG, TRNRETHOLD, TRNHISTORY, TRNHISTORICAL, SRCTRN_ID FROM TRNSHIST
UNION ALL SELECT TRNSLOG_ID, JOB_ID, TRN_ID, CAST(TRNSLOG_ID as NVARCHAR2(47)), KEY1, KEY2, KEY3, KEYID, CAST(TRNSLOG_ID as NVARCHAR2(47)), ARCKEY, RECTYPE, DESCR, TRNNAME, DOCTYPE, DOCSUBTYPE, ORIGUSER, CURRUSER, CURRGROUP, CURRROLE, CURRSUPER, CURRAPP_ID, STATUSCODE, TRANCODE, APPROVALSTATE, SECLEVEL, TRNERR_ID, INUSE, CUSTOMIZED, CREATETIME, BEGINTIME, TRNSTARTTIME, MODIFYTIME, TRNMODIFYTIME, ARCTIME, RETENTION, TRNENDTIME, ENDTIME, APPDATA, JURISDICTN, LOCID, QUEUEID, SUBLOCID, AGENCYID, FROMUSER, FROMTIME, FROMGROUP, TOTIME, TOUSER, TOGROUP, ROUTEDESC, PROCESSNAME, TRNAPPDATE001, TRNAPPDATE002, TRNAPPDATE003, TRNAPPDATE004, TRNAPPDATE005, TRNAPPDEC001, TRNAPPDEC002, TRNAPPDEC003, TRNAPPDEC004, TRNAPPDEC005, TRNAPPINT001, TRNAPPINT002, TRNAPPINT003, TRNAPPINT004, TRNAPPINT005, TRNAPPSTR001, TRNAPPSTR002, TRNAPPSTR003, TRNAPPSTR004, TRNAPPSTR005, TRNAPPSTR006, TRNAPPSTR007, TRNAPPSTR008, TRNAPPSTR009, TRNAPPSTR010, TRNAPPSTR011, TRNAPPSTR012, TRNAPPSTR013, TRNAPPSTR014, TRNAPPSTR015, TRNCUSDATE001, TRNCUSDATE002, TRNCUSDATE003, TRNCUSDATE004, TRNCUSDATE005, TRNCUSDATE006, TRNCUSDATE007, TRNCUSDATE008, TRNCUSDATE009, TRNCUSDATE010, TRNCUSDATE011, TRNCUSDATE012, TRNCUSDATE013, TRNCUSDATE014, TRNCUSDATE015, TRNCUSDEC001, TRNCUSDEC002, TRNCUSDEC003, TRNCUSDEC004, TRNCUSDEC005, TRNCUSINT001, TRNCUSINT002, TRNCUSINT003, TRNCUSINT004, TRNCUSINT005, TRNCUSSTR001, TRNCUSSTR002, TRNCUSSTR003, TRNCUSSTR004, TRNCUSSTR005, TRNCUSSTR006, TRNCUSSTR007, TRNCUSSTR008, TRNCUSSTR009, TRNCUSSTR010, TRNCUSSTR011, TRNCUSSTR012, TRNCUSSTR013, TRNCUSSTR014, TRNCUSSTR015, TRNCUSSTR016, TRNCUSSTR017, TRNCUSSTR018, TRNCUSSTR019, TRNCUSSTR020, ACTION, REASON_ID, TRNSTATUS, TRNRCPTOTAL, TRNRCPERR, TRNRCPSCH, TRNRCPPROC, TRNBCHTOTAL, TRNBCHERR, TRNBCHSCH, TRNBCHPROC, TRNDATATYPE, TRNDATAREF, TRNDATAXML, TRNDATABLOB, TRNDATASIZE, TRNNAPOLTYPE, TRNNAPOLREF, TRNNAPOLXML, TRNNAPOLBLOB, TRNNAPOLSIZE, TRNPRTLOGNAME, TRNDOLOG, TRNRETHOLD, TRNHISTORY, -1 AS TRNHISTORICAL, SRCTRN_ID FROM TRNSLOG WHERE TRNDOLOG=2;
